## Anti-Patterns to Avoid (from anti-patterns.md #15-#19c)

Before writing ANY frontend code, be aware of these 7 verified mistakes:

| #    | Anti-Pattern                                               | Correct                                                         | Severity |
|------|------------------------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------|----------|
| 15   | Bare `@zama-fhe/relayer-sdk` import                        | Use sub-path: `/web`, `/bundle`, or `/node`                     | HIGH     |
| 16   | `initFhevm()`                                              | `initSDK()`                                                      | HIGH     |
| 17   | `results.values[0]`                                        | `results.clearValues[handle]`                                    | HIGH     |
| 18   | `@fhevm/sdk`                                               | `@zama-fhe/relayer-sdk`                                          | HIGH     |
| 19   | Missing COOP/COEP headers                                  | Serve `same-origin` + `require-corp` (or `credentialless`)       | MEDIUM   |
| 19b  | Vite `optimizeDeps` rewrites SDK WASM URL to a 404         | `optimizeDeps.exclude: ["@zama-fhe/relayer-sdk"]`, `worker.format: "es"` | HIGH |
| 19c  | Next.js / Remix SSR: `ReferenceError: indexedDB is not defined` | `"use client"` + gate `initSDK` / `createInstance` behind `useEffect` | HIGH |

Load the full list: `.cursor/references/anti-patterns.md`

## Code Style (enforced on every TS / JS / TSX / JSX file)

- **No `//` or `///`.** All comments are block-style `/* */` or JSDoc `/** */`.
- **No em or en dashes.** U+2014 (EM DASH) and U+2013 (EN DASH) are banned.
  Use hyphen, colon, comma, parentheses, or rephrase.
- **File header** - open every source file with a JSDoc `@file` block:

  ```typescript
  /**
   * @file encrypt.ts
   * @description Browser-side encryption helpers for the counter dApp.
   */
  ```

- **Section dividers** are asterisk-bordered box comments, one line each:

  ```typescript
  /*************** SDK Init ***************/
  /*************** Encryption Helpers ***************/
  /*************** Wallet Connector ***************/
  ```

  At least 10 leading and 10 trailing `*`, Title Case label.

- **Exported functions / classes / hooks** carry a full JSDoc block.

  JSDoc / TSDoc is NOT NatSpec. Do not use `@notice`, `@dev`, `@inheritdoc`,
  or `@custom:*` in TypeScript - those are Solidity-only tags parsed by
  the Solidity compiler. In TS / JS, the description is the leading text
  (no tag), and you use standard JSDoc / TSDoc tags.

  Standard tags: plain leading description, `@param`, `@returns`,
  `@throws`, `@example`, `@deprecated`, `@see`, `@remarks` (TSDoc).

  ```typescript
  /**
   * Encrypt a euint64 input bound to the given contract / user.
   *
   * Handle order matches the `add*()` call order - when passing to the
   * contract, `handles[0]` corresponds to the first `add*()` call.
   *
   * @param contractAddr Destination contract (binds the proof).
   * @param userAddr User the input is attributed to.
   * @param amount Cleartext amount, bigint, fits in 64 bits.
   * @returns `{ handle, proof }` - pass both to the contract call.
   * @throws If `initSDK()` has not been awaited in the browser.
   */
  export async function encryptAmount(
    contractAddr: `0x${string}`,
    userAddr: `0x${string}`,
    amount: bigint,
  ): Promise<{ handle: Uint8Array; proof: Uint8Array }> { }
  ```

- **Inline comments** explain WHY, not WHAT. Spend them on non-obvious SDK
  behavior: handle order, `clearValues` vs `values`, COOP / COEP
  tradeoffs, Vite `optimizeDeps` WASM bug, `credentialless` vs
  `require-corp` with wallet connectors.

## Frontend Checklist

- [ ] Import uses sub-path `/web`, `/bundle`, or `/node` (WHY: bare import fails, no main export)
- [ ] Init is `initSDK()` not `initFhevm()` (WHY: initFhevm does not exist)
- [ ] Result field `clearValues` not `values` (WHY: actual type uses clearValues)
- [ ] COOP / COEP headers configured (WHY: WASM SharedArrayBuffer requires them)
- [ ] No `fhevmjs` or `@fhevm/sdk` imports (WHY: deprecated / does not exist)
- [ ] Zero `//` or `///` comments, block-style only (WHY: project rule)
- [ ] Zero em / en dashes (WHY: project rule)
- [ ] File opens with `@file` + `@description` JSDoc header (WHY: project rule)
- [ ] Section dividers are asterisk-box `/*************** Name ***************/` (WHY: preferred project style)

### Post-Delivery Grep (zero matches required)
```
FHEVM: from '@zama-fhe/relayer-sdk'[^/]|initFhevm|@fhevm/sdk|results\.values\[|fhevmjs|zama\.cloud
Style: ^\s*//[^\*]|^\s*///|[\x{2013}\x{2014}\x{1F680}\x{26A0}]
```

